  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, `SafeERC20`'s allowance-related functionality is restricted to a `safeApprove` function, which is vulnerable to the well-known non-zero approval issue in the ERC20 spec. We should:\r\n\r\n- add `safeIncreaseAllowance` and `safeDecreaseAllowance`, with `require` on the return value of the `ERC20` functions\r\n- add extra `require`s to `safeApprove` so that it only works if the new or old allowance are 0 (i.e. it only sets an initial allowance, or sets it to 0, which are the only safe scenarios).\r\n\r\nThis way, we'll be guiding users to the best practices regarding `ERC20` tokens.\r\n\r\nProps to @cwhinfrey and the Level K team for suggesting this!",
